While the wedding was about my now wife, and myself, it wouldn't have been the same without him.  It was a great event, and we had a blast.  My buddy brought his wife and child, and made great sacrifices to be there. It was one of the greatest events of my life, and we were beyond ecstatic they could make it. It was my wife's first time meeting him, as he lives a great distance away.  She hit it off with them very well, and we were both very thankful for not only them, but the way the event unfolded. He definitely fit in well and made for an enjoyable time. He has a sense of humor that is like mine and very raw, and it's pretty constant. My wife and I have already discussed and are planning a trip to go visit him and his family in the coming year.  His family and my family have begun to forge a bond that I hope will last a lifetime.  It was overall a very joyous and memorable day. I couldn't be happier, and am very thankful that my wife accepted him in such open arms. On the flip side of that, I'm happy his family embraced us so lovingly as well.

mostSurprising: my best friend flew over 1200 miles to attend.
story: Just a matter of months ago I got married for the first (and hopefully last) time in my life.  As one would expect, it was a very significant step, and a very special moment in my life.  We opted to not go too overboard, and had under 100 guests total.  Everything went very well, and the memory of that day will stay in my mind, and I'll cherish it for the rest of my life.  Besides our immediate family, I had my best friend come up from across the country to be my best man. I absolutely love him and his family, and cherish every moment we get to spend together. I don't get to see him too often, so when I do I take full advantage and try to enjoy every moment as much as possible.  Not only did he come with his daughter and wife, but his parents were there as well, as they are very important to me.  I was overwhelmed with the amount of people we had there, and probably felt as loved and important as I ever have in my life on account of all the people there. The only part that was a bit bothersome was with it being a wedding, and so many people, I didn't get much time to chat with each person, as I would have liked to. I've come to realize that's just how weddings are with so many people and only so much time, that it's part of the gig.  But beyond that, it was an amazing experience, and I enjoyed myself a great deal. My wife looked gorgeous (as usual), and I am overly thankful to spend the rest of my life with her.  The photographer did an excellent job, and I helped her out by being a joker and keeping people laughing and smiling which helped with pictures. It was a great day, and I am still ecstatic that I got to share our special day with such great people.  The caterer did fantastic, and the venue we used was absolutely perfect, and extremely affordable.  It did rain a little bit, but we managed to dodge the brunt of it, which was good as we had planned and hoped to have it outdoors.  We did have a backup plan if we would have to move it inside, but we were hoping that we could keep it outdoors. All in all it will go down as one of the most memorable and enjoyable days of my life.
summary: A few months back, I got married. The wedding went very well, and I will never forget the day. Besides my bride, having my buddy fly in from over 1200 miles away stands out as the most shocking (in a good way) part of the whole wedding.

The caterer did fantastic, and the venue we used was absolutely perfect, and extremely affordable. It did rain a little bit, but we managed to dodge the brunt of it, which was good as we had planned and hoped to have it outdoors. I've come to realize that's just how weddings are with so many people and only so much time, that it's part of the gig. I don't get to see him too often, so when I do I take full advantage and try to enjoy every moment as much as possible. We opted to not go too overboard, and had under 100 guests total. Not only did he come with his daughter and wife, but his parents were there as well, as they are very important to me. But beyond that, it was an amazing experience, and I enjoyed myself a great deal. It was a great day, and I am still ecstatic that I got to share our special day with such great people. The photographer did an excellent job, and I helped her out by being a joker and keeping people laughing and smiling which helped with pictures. Everything went very well, and the memory of that day will stay in my mind, and I'll cherish it for the rest of my life. I was overwhelmed with the amount of people we had there, and probably felt as loved and important as I ever have in my life on account of all the people there. I absolutely love him and his family, and cherish every moment we get to spend together. The only part that was a bit bothersome was with it being a wedding, and so many people, I didn't get much time to chat with each person, as I would have liked to. My wife looked gorgeous (as usual), and I am overly thankful to spend the rest of my life with her. Just a matter of months ago I got married for the first (and hopefully last) time in my life.
summary: A few months back, I got married. The wedding went very well, and I will never forget the day. Besides my bride, having my buddy fly in from over 1200 miles away stands out as the most shocking (in a good way) part of the whole wedding.

mostSurprising: my best friend flew over 1200 miles to attend.
story: I got married a few months ago, and it was a very exciting event.  One of the most (if not the most) memorable parts was my best friend of over 20 years flying in from over 1200 miles to be in the wedding. While the wedding was about my now wife, and myself, it wouldn't have been the same without him.  It was a great event, and we had a blast.  My buddy brought his wife and child, and made great sacrifices to be there. It was one of the greatest events of my life, and we were beyond ecstatic they could make it. It was my wife's first time meeting him, as he lives a great distance away.  She hit it off with them very well, and we were both very thankful for not only them, but the way the event unfolded. He definitely fit in well and made for an enjoyable time. He has a sense of humor that is like mine and very raw, and it's pretty constant. He was telling jokes to everyone, and everyone seemed to appreciate it, except for one person, but I won't waste the time to add them into this. My wife and I have already discussed and are planning a trip to go visit him and his family in the coming year.  His family and my family have begun to forge a bond that I hope will last a lifetime.  It was overall a very joyous and memorable day. I couldn't be happier, and am very thankful that my wife accepted him in such open arms. On the flip side of that, I'm happy his family embraced us so lovingly as well.
summary: A few months back, I got married. The wedding went very well, and I will never forget the day. Besides my bride, having my buddy fly in from over 1200 miles away stands out as the most shocking (in a good way) part of the whole wedding.

mostSurprising: my best friend flew over 1200 miles to attend.
story: Just a matter of months ago I got married for the first (and hopefully last) time in my life.  As one would expect, it was a very significant step, and a very special moment in my life.  We opted to not go too overboard, and had under 100 guests total.  Everything went very well, and the memory of that day will stay in my mind, and I'll cherish it for the rest of my life.  Besides our immediate family, I had my best friend come up from across the country to be my best man. I absolutely love him and his family, and cherish every moment we get to spend together. I don't get to see him too often, so when I do I take full advantage and try to enjoy every moment as much as possible.  Not only did he come with his daughter and wife, but his parents were there as well, as they are very important to me.  I was overwhelmed with the amount of people we had there, and probably felt as loved and important as I ever have in my life on account of all the people there. The only part that was a bit bothersome was with it being a wedding, and so many people, I didn't get much time to chat with each person, as I would have liked to. I've come to realize that's just how weddings are with so many people and only so much time, that it's part of the gig.  But beyond that, it was an amazing experience, and I enjoyed myself a great deal. My wife looked gorgeous (as usual), and I am overly thankful to spend the rest of my life with her.  The photographer did an excellent job, and I helped her out by being a joker and keeping people laughing and smiling which helped with pictures. It was a great day, and I am still ecstatic that I got to share our special day with such great people.  The caterer did fantastic, and the venue we used was absolutely perfect, and extremely affordable.  It did rain a little bit, but we managed to dodge the brunt of it, which was good as we had planned and hoped to have it outdoors.  We did have a backup plan if we would have to move it inside, but we were hoping that we could keep it outdoors. All in all it will go down as one of the most memorable and enjoyable days of my life.
summary: A few months back, I got married. The wedding went very well, and I will never forget the day. Besides my bride, having my buddy fly in from over 1200 miles away stands out as the most shocking (in a good way) part of the whole wedding.

It did rain a little bit, but we managed to dodge the brunt of it, which was good as we had planned and hoped to have it outdoors. I absolutely love him and his family, and cherish every moment we get to spend together. Besides our immediate family, I had my best friend come up from across the country to be my best man. The only part that was a bit bothersome was with it being a wedding, and so many people, I didn't get much time to chat with each person, as I would have liked to. I was overwhelmed with the amount of people we had there, and probably felt as loved and important as I ever have in my life on account of all the people there. mostSurprising: my best friend flew over 1200 miles to attend.
story: I got married a few months ago, and it was a very exciting event.  One of the most (if not the most) memorable parts was my best friend of over 20 years flying in from over 1200 miles to be in the wedding. While the wedding was about my now wife, and myself, it wouldn't have been the same without him.  It was a great event, and we had a blast.  My buddy brought his wife and child, and made great sacrifices to be there. It was one of the greatest events of my life, and we were beyond ecstatic they could make it. It was my wife's first time meeting him, as he lives a great distance away.  She hit it off with them very well, and we were both very thankful for not only them, but the way the event unfolded. He definitely fit in well and made for an enjoyable time. He has a sense of humor that is like mine and very raw, and it's pretty constant. He was telling jokes to everyone, and everyone seemed to appreciate it, except for one person, but I won't waste the time to add them into this. My wife and I have already discussed and are planning a trip to go visit him and his family in the coming year.  His family and my family have begun to forge a bond that I hope will last a lifetime.  It was overall a very joyous and memorable day. I couldn't be happier, and am very thankful that my wife accepted him in such open arms. On the flip side of that, I'm happy his family embraced us so lovingly as well.
summary: A few months back, I got married. The wedding went very well, and I will never forget the day. Besides my bride, having my buddy fly in from over 1200 miles away stands out as the most shocking (in a good way) part of the whole wedding.

mostSurprising: my best friend flew over 1200 miles to attend.
story: Just a matter of months ago I got married for the first (and hopefully last) time in my life.  As one would expect, it was a very significant step, and a very special moment in my life.  We opted to not go too overboard, and had under 100 guests total.  Everything went very well, and the memory of that day will stay in my mind, and I'll cherish it for the rest of my life.  Besides our immediate family, I had my best friend come up from across the country to be my best man. I absolutely love him and his family, and cherish every moment we get to spend together. I don't get to see him too often, so when I do I take full advantage and try to enjoy every moment as much as possible.  Not only did he come with his daughter and wife, but his parents were there as well, as they are very important to me.  I was overwhelmed with the amount of people we had there, and probably felt as loved and important as I ever have in my life on account of all the people there. The only part that was a bit bothersome was with it being a wedding, and so many people, I didn't get much time to chat with each person, as I would have liked to. I've come to realize that's just how weddings are with so many people and only so much time, that it's part of the gig.  But beyond that, it was an amazing experience, and I enjoyed myself a great deal. My wife looked gorgeous (as usual), and I am overly thankful to spend the rest of my life with her.  The photographer did an excellent job, and I helped her out by being a joker and keeping people laughing and smiling which helped with pictures. It was a great day, and I am still ecstatic that I got to share our special day with such great people.  The caterer did fantastic, and the venue we used was absolutely perfect, and extremely affordable.  It did rain a little bit, but we managed to dodge the brunt of it, which was good as we had planned and hoped to have it outdoors.  We did have a backup plan if we would have to move it inside, but we were hoping that we could keep it outdoors. All in all it will go down as one of the most memorable and enjoyable days of my life.
summary: A few months back, I got married. The wedding went very well, and I will never forget the day. Besides my bride, having my buddy fly in from over 1200 miles away stands out as the most shocking (in a good way) part of the whole wedding.

The caterer did fantastic, and the venue we used was absolutely perfect, and extremely affordable. Everything went very well, and the memory of that day will stay in my mind, and I'll cherish it for the rest of my life. The photographer did an excellent job, and I helped her out by being a joker and keeping people laughing and smiling which helped with pictures. But beyond that, it was an amazing experience, and I enjoyed myself a great deal. Just a matter of months ago I got married for the first (and hopefully last) time in my life. My wife looked gorgeous (as usual), and I am overly thankful to spend the rest of my life with her. Besides our immediate family, I had my best friend come up from across the country to be my best man. We opted to not go too overboard, and had under 100 guests total. I've come to realize that's just how weddings are with so many people and only so much time, that it's part of the gig. I absolutely love him and his family, and cherish every moment we get to spend together. We did have a backup plan if we would have to move it inside, but we were hoping that we could keep it outdoors. It was a great day, and I am still ecstatic that I got to share our special day with such great people. Not only did he come with his daughter and wife, but his parents were there as well, as they are very important to me. All in all it will go down as one of the most memorable and enjoyable days of my life. It did rain a little bit, but we managed to dodge the brunt of it, which was good as we had planned and hoped to have it outdoors. I don't get to see him too often, so when I do I take full advantage and try to enjoy every moment as much as possible. The only part that was a bit bothersome was with it being a wedding, and so many people, I didn't get much time to chat with each person, as I would have liked to.
summary: A few months back, I got married. The wedding went very well, and I will never forget the day. Besides my bride, having my buddy fly in from over 1200 miles away stands out as the most shocking (in a good way) part of the whole wedding.

I was overwhelmed with the amount of people we had there, and probably felt as loved and important as I ever have in my life on account of all the people there. Besides our immediate family, I had my best friend come up from across the country to be my best man. The photographer did an excellent job, and I helped her out by being a joker and keeping people laughing and smiling which helped with pictures. I've come to realize that's just how weddings are with so many people and only so much time, that it's part of the gig. As one would expect, it was a very significant step, and a very special moment in my life. But beyond that, it was an amazing experience, and I enjoyed myself a great deal. I absolutely love him and his family, and cherish every moment we get to spend together. The only part that was a bit bothersome was with it being a wedding, and so many people, I didn't get much time to chat with each person, as I would have liked to. We did have a backup plan if we would have to move it inside, but we were hoping that we could keep it outdoors. It was a great day, and I am still ecstatic that I got to share our special day with such great people. All in all it will go down as one of the most memorable and enjoyable days of my life. My wife looked gorgeous (as usual), and I am overly thankful to spend the rest of my life with her. I don't get to see him too often, so when I do I take full advantage and try to enjoy every moment as much as possible. The caterer did fantastic, and the venue we used was absolutely perfect, and extremely affordable. Not only did he come with his daughter and wife, but his parents were there as well, as they are very important to me. Just a matter of months ago I got married for the first (and hopefully last) time in my life.

Besides our immediate family, I had my best friend come up from across the country to be my best man. I absolutely love him and his family, and cherish every moment we get to spend together. I don't get to see him too often, so when I do I take full advantage and try to enjoy every moment as much as possible.  Not only did he come with his daughter and wife, but his parents were there as well, as they are very important to me.  I was overwhelmed with the amount of people we had there, and probably felt as loved and important as I ever have in my life on account of all the people there. The photographer did an excellent job, and I helped her out by being a joker and keeping people laughing and smiling which helped with pictures. The caterer did fantastic, and the venue we used was absolutely perfect, and extremely affordable.  It did rain a little bit, but we managed to dodge the brunt of it, which was good as we had planned and hoped to have it outdoors.  We did have a backup plan if we would have to move it inside, but we were hoping that we could keep it outdoors. All in all it will go down as one of the most memorable and enjoyable days of my life.

mostSurprising: my best friend flew over 1200 miles to attend.
story: I got married a few months ago, and it was a very exciting event.  One of the most (if not the most) memorable parts was my best friend of over 20 years flying in from over 1200 miles to be in the wedding. While the wedding was about my now wife, and myself, it wouldn't have been the same without him.  It was a great event, and we had a blast.  My buddy brought his wife and child, and made great sacrifices to be there. It was one of the greatest events of my life, and we were beyond ecstatic they could make it. It was my wife's first time meeting him, as he lives a great distance away.  She hit it off with them very well, and we were both very thankful for not only them, but the way the event unfolded. He definitely fit in well and made for an enjoyable time. He has a sense of humor that is like mine and very raw, and it's pretty constant. He was telling jokes to everyone, and everyone seemed to appreciate it, except for one person, but I won't waste the time to add them into this. My wife and I have already discussed and are planning a trip to go visit him and his family in the coming year.  His family and my family have begun to forge a bond that I hope will last a lifetime.  It was overall a very joyous and memorable day. I couldn't be happier, and am very thankful that my wife accepted him in such open arms. On the flip side of that, I'm happy his family embraced us so lovingly as well.
summary: A few months back, I got married. The wedding went very well, and I will never forget the day. Besides my bride, having my buddy fly in from over 1200 miles away stands out as the most shocking (in a good way) part of the whole wedding.

mostSurprising: my best friend flew over 1200 miles to attend.
story: Just a matter of months ago I got married for the first (and hopefully last) time in my life.  As one would expect, it was a very significant step, and a very special moment in my life.  We opted to not go too overboard, and had under 100 guests total.  Everything went very well, and the memory of that day will stay in my mind, and I'll cherish it for the rest of my life.  Besides our immediate family, I had my best friend come up from across the country to be my best man. I absolutely love him and his family, and cherish every moment we get to spend together. I don't get to see him too often, so when I do I take full advantage and try to enjoy every moment as much as possible.  Not only did he come with his daughter and wife, but his parents were there as well, as they are very important to me.  I was overwhelmed with the amount of people we had there, and probably felt as loved and important as I ever have in my life on account of all the people there. The only part that was a bit bothersome was with it being a wedding, and so many people, I didn't get much time to chat with each person, as I would have liked to. I've come to realize that's just how weddings are with so many people and only so much time, that it's part of the gig.  But beyond that, it was an amazing experience, and I enjoyed myself a great deal. My wife looked gorgeous (as usual), and I am overly thankful to spend the rest of my life with her.  The photographer did an excellent job, and I helped her out by being a joker and keeping people laughing and smiling which helped with pictures. It was a great day, and I am still ecstatic that I got to share our special day with such great people.  The caterer did fantastic, and the venue we used was absolutely perfect, and extremely affordable.  It did rain a little bit, but we managed to dodge the brunt of it, which was good as we had planned and hoped to have it outdoors.  We did have a backup plan if we would have to move it inside, but we were hoping that we could keep it outdoors. All in all it will go down as one of the most memorable and enjoyable days of my life.
summary: A few months back, I got married. The wedding went very well, and I will never forget the day. Besides my bride, having my buddy fly in from over 1200 miles away stands out as the most shocking (in a good way) part of the whole wedding.

I was overwhelmed with the amount of people we had there, and probably felt as loved and important as I ever have in my life on account of all the people there. As one would expect, it was a very significant step, and a very special moment in my life. My wife looked gorgeous (as usual), and I am overly thankful to spend the rest of my life with her. It was a great day, and I am still ecstatic that I got to share our special day with such great people. We did have a backup plan if we would have to move it inside, but we were hoping that we could keep it outdoors. The photographer did an excellent job, and I helped her out by being a joker and keeping people laughing and smiling which helped with pictures. It did rain a little bit, but we managed to dodge the brunt of it, which was good as we had planned and hoped to have it outdoors. Just a matter of months ago I got married for the first (and hopefully last) time in my life. I've come to realize that's just how weddings are with so many people and only so much time, that it's part of the gig. Not only did he come with his daughter and wife, but his parents were there as well, as they are very important to me. Besides our immediate family, I had my best friend come up from across the country to be my best man. The caterer did fantastic, and the venue we used was absolutely perfect, and extremely affordable. But beyond that, it was an amazing experience, and I enjoyed myself a great deal. All in all it will go down as one of the most memorable and enjoyable days of my life. We opted to not go too overboard, and had under 100 guests total. I don't get to see him too often, so when I do I take full advantage and try to enjoy every moment as much as possible. The only part that was a bit bothersome was with it being a wedding, and so many people, I didn't get much time to chat with each person, as I would have liked to.

story: It was a great day, and I am still ecstatic that I got to share our special day with such great people. But beyond that, it was an amazing experience, and I enjoyed myself a great deal. We did have a backup plan if we would have to move it inside, but we were hoping that we could keep it outdoors. It did rain a little bit, but we managed to dodge the brunt of it, which was good as we had planned and hoped to have it outdoors. Just a matter of months ago I got married for the first (and hopefully last) time in my life. Everything went very well, and the memory of that day will stay in my mind, and I'll cherish it for the rest of my life. As one would expect, it was a very significant step, and a very special moment in my life. I was overwhelmed with the amount of people we had there, and probably felt as loved and important as I ever have in my life on account of all the people there. I don't get to see him too often, so when I do I take full advantage and try to enjoy every moment as much as possible. My wife looked gorgeous (as usual), and I am overly thankful to spend the rest of my life with her. The photographer did an excellent job, and I helped her out by being a joker and keeping people laughing and smiling which helped with pictures. All in all it will go down as one of the most memorable and enjoyable days of my life. Not only did he come with his daughter and wife, but his parents were there as well, as they are very important to me. The caterer did fantastic, and the venue we used was absolutely perfect, and extremely affordable. I absolutely love him and his family, and cherish every moment we get to spend together. We opted to not go too overboard, and had under 100 guests total. Besides our immediate family, I had my best friend come up from across the country to be my best man. The only part that was a bit bothersome was with it being a wedding, and so many people, I didn't get much time to chat with each person, as I would have liked to. I've come to realize that's just how weddings are with so many people and only so much time, that it's part of the gig.

mostSurprising: my best friend flew over 1200 miles to attend.
story: Just a matter of months ago I got married for the first (and hopefully last) time in my life.  As one would expect, it was a very significant step, and a very special moment in my life.  We opted to not go too overboard, and had under 100 guests total.  Everything went very well, and the memory of that day will stay in my mind, and I'll cherish it for the rest of my life.  Besides our immediate family, I had my best friend come up from across the country to be my best man. I absolutely love him and his family, and cherish every moment we get to spend together. I don't get to see him too often, so when I do I take full advantage and try to enjoy every moment as much as possible.  Not only did he come with his daughter and wife, but his parents were there as well, as they are very important to me.  I was overwhelmed with the amount of people we had there, and probably felt as loved and important as I ever have in my life on account of all the people there. The only part that was a bit bothersome was with it being a wedding, and so many people, I didn't get much time to chat with each person, as I would have liked to. I've come to realize that's just how weddings are with so many people and only so much time, that it's part of the gig.  But beyond that, it was an amazing experience, and I enjoyed myself a great deal. My wife looked gorgeous (as usual), and I am overly thankful to spend the rest of my life with her.  The photographer did an excellent job, and I helped her out by being a joker and keeping people laughing and smiling which helped with pictures. It was a great day, and I am still ecstatic that I got to share our special day with such great people.  The caterer did fantastic, and the venue we used was absolutely perfect, and extremely affordable.  It did rain a little bit, but we managed to dodge the brunt of it, which was good as we had planned and hoped to have it outdoors.  We did have a backup plan if we would have to move it inside, but we were hoping that we could keep it outdoors. All in all it will go down as one of the most memorable and enjoyable days of my life.

It was a great day, and I am still ecstatic that I got to share our special day with such great people. We opted to not go too overboard, and had under 100 guests total. Just a matter of months ago I got married for the first (and hopefully last) time in my life. The caterer did fantastic, and the venue we used was absolutely perfect, and extremely affordable. Not only did he come with his daughter and wife, but his parents were there as well, as they are very important to me. As one would expect, it was a very significant step, and a very special moment in my life. Everything went very well, and the memory of that day will stay in my mind, and I'll cherish it for the rest of my life. But beyond that, it was an amazing experience, and I enjoyed myself a great deal. The only part that was a bit bothersome was with it being a wedding, and so many people, I didn't get much time to chat with each person, as I would have liked to. We did have a backup plan if we would have to move it inside, but we were hoping that we could keep it outdoors. It did rain a little bit, but we managed to dodge the brunt of it, which was good as we had planned and hoped to have it outdoors. I don't get to see him too often, so when I do I take full advantage and try to enjoy every moment as much as possible. I was overwhelmed with the amount of people we had there, and probably felt as loved and important as I ever have in my life on account of all the people there. All in all it will go down as one of the most memorable and enjoyable days of my life. I've come to realize that's just how weddings are with so many people and only so much time, that it's part of the gig. My wife looked gorgeous (as usual), and I am overly thankful to spend the rest of my life with her. I absolutely love him and his family, and cherish every moment we get to spend together.
summary: A few months back, I got married. The wedding went very well, and I will never forget the day. Besides my bride, having my buddy fly in from over 1200 miles away stands out as the most shocking (in a good way) part of the whole wedding.

story: Brad and i got married today. But i do understand why everyone says that now. The catering was fantastic. We had a traditional catholic wedding. Everyone seemed to enjoy themselves. It has been four years in making and we couldn't have imagined a more perfect wedding. Today is the happiest day of my life. It was a happy time with family. It was particularly surprising considering he was combating cancer for a while now. But all those didn't matter today. Everyone was there- even uncle larry showed up! It was about us, and our new beginning.
summary: My fiance and I got married after almost four years of dating. We had a Catholic wedding and then spent time eating and socializing with family members and other loved ones.
